.SH NAME
Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP85 \- BIP85 (deterministic entropy) implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&        use Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP85;
\&
\&        my $bip85 = Bitcoin::Crypto::BIP85\->new(
\&                key => $extended_private_key,
\&        );
\&
\&        # get raw bytestring seed
\&        my $seed = $bip85\->derive_entropy("m/0\*(Aq/0\*(Aq");
\&
\&        # get a mnemonic
\&        my $mnemonic = $bip85\->derive_mnemonic(index => 0);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module implements
BIP85 <https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0085.mediawiki>,
enabling deterministic entropy generation from a master key.
.PP
It currently implements the following applications from the BIP85 spec:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`BIP39\*(C'\fR: "derive_mnemonic"
.Sp
This application requires extra CPAN wordlists for Bitcoin::BIP39 to handle
other languages than \f(CW\*(C`en\*(C'\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`HD\-Seed WIF\*(C'\fR: "derive_prv"
.Sp
This application returns a private key instead of a WIF, but can be serialized
using "to_wif" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Key::Private.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`XPRV\*(C'\fR: "derive_extprv"
.Sp
This application returns an extended private key instead of its serialized
version, but can be serialized using
"to_serialized" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Key::ExtPrivate.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`HEX\*(C'\fR: "derive_bytes"
.Sp
This application returns a bytestring instead of a hex string in order to be
coherent with other similar Bitcoin::Crypto methods. It can be represented as
hex using "to_format" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Util.
.PP
Missing BIP85 applications can be implemented using "derive_entropy" with
proper derivation path and entropy length.
.SH INTERFACE
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
.SS Attributes
.IX Subsection "Attributes"
\fIkey\fR
.IX Subsection "key"
.PP
