.PP
\fIderive_entropy\fR
.IX Subsection "derive_entropy"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $bytestr = $object\->derive_entropy($path, $length = undef)
.Ve
.PP
Returns entropy derived from the master key using
\&\f(CW$path\fR, which can be a standard string derivation path like
\&\f(CW\*(C`m/83696968\*(Aq/0\*(Aq/0\*(Aq\*(C'\fR or an instance of Bitcoin::Crypto::DerivationPath. The
derivation path must be fully hardened, as specified in the BIP.
.PP
Optional \f(CW$length\fR is the desired length of the entropy \fBin bytes\fR. If not
provided, full \f(CW64\fR bytes of entropy will be returned. If provided and less
than \f(CW64\fR, the entropy will be truncated to the derired length. If greater
than \f(CW64\fR, the \f(CW\*(C`DRNG\*(C'\fR algorithm defined in BIP85 will be used to stretch the
entropy to this size.
.PP
\fIderive_mnemonic\fR
.IX Subsection "derive_mnemonic"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $mnemonic = $object\->derive_mnemonic(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Derives mnemonic from the master key. \f(CW%args\fR can be any combination of:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`words\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The number of words to generate. Can be either \f(CW12\fR, \f(CW18\fR or \f(CW24\fR. Default: \f(CW24\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`language\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The language to use. See Bitcoin::BIP39 for more info about this argument. Default: \f(CW\*(C`en\*(C'\fR.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`index\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The generation index. Must be a non\-negative integer. Default: \f(CW0\fR
.PP
\fIderive_prv\fR
.IX Subsection "derive_prv"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $prv = $object\->derive_prv(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Derives private key from the master key. The key can immediately be
serialized using \f(CW\*(C`\->to_wif\*(C'\fR to match BIP85 spec for this
application. \f(CW%args\fR can be any combination of:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`index\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The generation index. Must be a non\-negative integer. Default: \f(CW0\fR
.PP
\fIderive_extprv\fR
.IX Subsection "derive_extprv"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $extprv = $object\->derive_extprv(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Derives an extended private key from the master key. The key can immediately be
serialized using \f(CW\*(C`\->to_serialized\*(C'\fR to match BIP85 spec for this
application. \f(CW%args\fR can be any combination of:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`index\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The generation index. Must be a non\-negative integer. Default: \f(CW0\fR
.PP
\fIderive_bytes\fR
.IX Subsection "derive_bytes"
.PP
.Vb 1
\&        $bytestr = $object\->derive_bytes(%args)
.Ve
.PP
Derives a number of bytes from the master key. The key can immediately be
serialized as hex using "to_format" in Bitcoin::Crypto::Util to match BIP85 spec
for this application. \f(CW%args\fR can be any combination of:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`bytes\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The number of bytes to generate. Must be between \f(CW16\fR and \f(CW64\fR, inclusive.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`index\*(C'\fR
.Sp
The generation index. Must be a non\-negative integer. Default: \f(CW0\fR
